generation:
Here's an example code snippet that you can use to create the play and reset buttons at the bottom left of your screen:
```
import React from 'react';
import { FaPlay, FaStepBackward } from 'react-icons/fa';

function PlayResetButtons() {
  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={() => playAudio()}>
        <FaPlay />
      </button>
      <button onClick={() => resetAudio()}>
        <FaStepBackward />
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```
In this code, we're importing the `FaPlay` and `FaStepBackward` icons from the `react-icons/fa` library. We're then creating a `PlayResetButtons` component that renders two buttons with these icons. The `onClick` event handlers for each button call the `playAudio` and `resetAudio` functions, respectively.

You can then use the `PlayResetButtons` component in your main component like this:
```
function App() {
  // ...

  return (
    <div>
      <PlayResetButtons />
      {/* ... other components ... */}
    </div>
  );
}
```
This will render the play and reset buttons at the bottom left of your screen. <|end|>
